data.enText: a musical instrument that you hold in both hands to produce sounds. You press the two ends together and pull them apart and press buttons and/or keys to produce the different notes.

simple_means.memory_skill: ac 加强 + cord 心，心脏 + ion 表物 → 抒发心声〔的琴〕→ 手风琴

tr: the reeds are made to vibrate by air from the bellows controlled by the player

value.def: An accordion is a musical instrument in the shape of a fairly large box which you hold in your hands. You play the accordion by pressing keys or buttons on either side while moving the two sides together and apart. Accordions are used especially to play traditional popular music.
